However, Lithuanian men admit that there are a series of circumstances for which they are more likely to not use a condom than in other situations, e.g., if they are not upset with partner or there is a belief that their sexual partner very rarely has sex with another. More than half (51.1 %) of men admitted that they would choose not to use a condom, if they knew that a woman could not become pregnant. Forty percent of men admitted that if a girl/woman refused to have sex with a man and/or put a condom, they would choose not to use a condom, because he trusted the girl/woman or did not believe that a girl/woman deliberately refuses to have sex with a man to cause the pregnancy.
